pted onto the **Broadcast Engineering & Technical Operations Bootcamp** at Cardiff and Vale College (7th–16th April). This is a specialized, industry-led programme that directly aligns with my background in IT and Cloud Engineering, and it is a critical step for me to transition into the high-growth broadcast sector in Wales.\n327: >\n328: > As this is an intensive, in-person programme based in Cardiff, I will need to be on-site for the duration of the training. I am requesting your support via the Restart Programme to help cover the costs of:\n329: > 1. Travel expenses to/from the college site.\n330: > 2. Temporary accommodation for the 6 days of training.\n331: >\n332: > Please let me know the process for formalizing this request or if you need any further information to approve this training support. \n333: >\n334: > Best regards,\n335: > Andrea Enning\n336: > 07480261369\n337: \n338: ---\n339: \n340: ### Email 2: To the College (Your \"Insurance\" Focus)\n341: **Why this works:** It is purely administrative. You are not asking questions; you are just providing info. This ensures that if they need to send you login details or joining instructions, they go to the right place.\n342: \n343: **Send to:** `info@cavc.ac.uk` (or the specific email of the admissions/enrollment team if you have it)\n344: \n345: > **Subject: Follow-up: Application for Broadcast Engineering Bootcamp - Student ID 730602**\n346: >\n347: > Dear Admissions Team,\n348: >\n349: > Following my call with Wendy earlier today, I am writing to confirm my contact details for my application to the **Broadcast Engineering & Technical Operations Bootcamp**.\n350: >\n351: > As I have recently relocated to Cardiff to focus on this programme, please ensure my student record is updated with the following contact address for any correspondence:\n352: >\n353: > **[Insert your friend's Cardiff address here]**\n354: >\n355: > Thank you for your assistance in processing my application. I look forward to receiving 