      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\Andrea_Enning_Master_CV.tex</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: % --- UNIVERSAL PREAMBLE BLOCK ---\n2: \\documentclass[12pt,a4paper,sans]{moderncv}\n3: \n4: % ModernCV themes\n5: \\moderncvstyle{classic}\n6: \\moderncvcolor{blue}\n7: \n8: % Character encoding\n9: \\usepackage[utf8]{inputenc}\n10: \n11: % Adjust the page margins\n12: \\usepackage{geometry}\n13: \\geometry{scale=0.86, top=1.2cm, bottom=1.2cm, left=1.2cm, right=1.2cm}\n14: \n15: % Line spacing\n16: \\usepackage{setspace}\n17: \\setstretch{1.33}\n18: \n19: % Define Custom Brand Colours\n20: \\definecolor{primary}{HTML}{025940}\n21: \\definecolor{bodytext}{HTML}{404040}\n22: \\definecolor{accentgreen}{HTML}{1DAA61}\n23: \\definecolor{linkblue}{HTML}{467886}\n24: \n25: % Override moderncv section style\n26: \\makeatletter\n27: \\RenewDocumentCommand{\\section}{sm}{%\n28:   \\par\\addvspace{2.5ex}%\n29:   \\phantomsection{}%\n30:   \\addcontentsline{toc}{section}{#2}%\n31:   \\parbox[t]{\\hintscolumnwidth}{\\strut\\raggedleft\\raisebox{\\baseletterheight}{\\color{primary}\\rule{\\hintscolumnwidth}{0.95ex}}}%\n32:   \\hspace{\\separatorcolumnwidth}%\n33:   \\parbox[t]{\\maincolumnwidth}{\\strut\\sectionstyle{#2}}%\n34:   \\par\\nobreak\\addvspace{1ex}\\@afterheading}%\n35: \\makeatother\n36: \n37: % Personal Information\n38: \\name{Andrea}{Enning}\n39: \\title{Co-Founder \\& Cloud Architect | AI-Native Product Lead | AWS Certified}\n40: \\address{Nottinghamshire, United Kingdom}{}\n41: \\phone[mobile]{\\href{tel:+4407480261369}{+44 07480 261369}}\n42: \\email{andiekobbietks@outlook.com}\n43: \n44: % Header Links\n45: \\extrainfo{\n46:     \\href{https://www.linkedin.com/in/andiekobbietks}{\\textcolor{linkblue}{linkedin.com/in/andiekobbietks}} \\textbullet{}\n47:     \\href{https://github.com/andiekobbietks}{\\textcolor{accentgreen}{github.com/andiekobbietks}}\n48: }\n49: \n50: % --- CONTENT ---\n51: \\begin{document}\n52: \\makecvtitle\n53: \n54: \\section{Professional Profile}\n55: \\cvitem{}{Co-Founder \\& Cloud Architect of Getaway AI, a multi-agent group travel planning application deployed on AWS Bedrock with real-time itinerary generation. Built and shipped the production system from architecture to deployment, managing the full infrastructure lifecycle including VPC design, IAM policies, Lambda orchestration, and Bedrock model integration. I conceived the product, recruited the team, secured resources, and continued development solo after the technical co-founder departed in September 2025.}\n56: \\cvitem{}{AWS re/Start graduate with hands-on cloud engineering expertise spanning VPC networking, IAM policy design, Lambda serverless architecture, and infrastructure-as-code automation. My dissertation---an AI teaching assistant using RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) architecture---achieved First Class Honours and demonstrated practical deployment of LLMs in educational contexts. I bring 18+ months of insider access to Tramshed Tech (Cardiff's largest tech hub), BYP Network co-lead position, and AWS Activate credits secured for Getaway AI.}\n57: \\cvitem{}{Published contributor to the EU Horizon 2020 Marie Curie MIDIC Project and the British Journal of Sociology, validating high-level Intercultural Competence (IC) and strategic navigation of complex socio-technical landscapes. Community Board Member \\& Tech Strategist for FirstGens CIC, architecting the data strategy underpinning their 2023-24 Impact Report and UCAS First-Generation Students Guidance.}\n58: \n59: \\section{Core Competencies}\n60: \\cvitem{Cloud \\& AI}{AWS Bedrock (Nova Lite, Haiku 4.5, Sonnet 4.6), Lambda, VPC, IAM, S3, CloudFormation, API Gateway; NVIDIA Inception (NIM APIs); Azure Active Directory; GCP; Oracle Cloud Always Free Tier; RAG Architecture; Prompt Engineering; Multi-Agent Orchestration.}\n61: \\cvitem{Software Dev}{Python (FastAPI/Pandas), JavaScript (React/Next.js), HTML5/CSS3, Git/GitHub, MySQL, PowerShell, Bash, Docker, Kubernetes, VMware, LAMP Stack, API Design, Agile/Scrum.}\n62: \\cvitem{Security \\& Ops}{Wazuh SIEM (Zero Trust Architecture), Azure Active Directory, Microsoft 365 Admin, GDPR Compliance, Information Security Awareness, ITIL Best Practices.}\n63: \\cvitem{Training \\& Leadership}{Curriculum Design (WJEC/IfATE), CPD Delivery, Formative Assessment, Stakeholder Management, Cross-Functional Team Leadership, Public Speaking, Intercultural Competence.}\n64: \n65: \\section{Professional Experience}\n66: \n67: \\cventry{Sept 2025--Present}{Co-Founder \\& Cloud Architect}{Getaway AI}{Remote / Nottinghamshire}{}{\n68: \\begin{itemize}\n69:     \\item \\textbf{Product Vision:} Conceived, designed, and shipped a multi-agent group travel planning application with real-time itinerary generation, flight search, hotel booking, and activity recommendations powered by AWS Bedrock AI models.\n70:     \\item \\textbf{Cloud Architecture:} Designed and deployed the full AWS infrastructure including VPC networking, IAM policy management, Lambda serverless functions, S3 storage, API Gateway endpoints, and Bedrock model orchestration for Nova Lite, Claude Haiku 4.5, and Sonnet 4.6.\n71:     \\item \\textbf{Technical Leadership:} Sole technical decision-maker after co-founder departure; managed product roadmap, security architecture, and deployment pipeline. Secured AWS Activate credits (\\$5,000) and NVIDIA Inception membership.\n72:     \\item \\textbf{Open Source \\& Community:} Built GitHub repository (Getaway-AI-Assistant) with multi-agent orchestration, integrated MCP Apps for distribution, and developed scratchpad skill for zero-config coding assistance.\n73:     \\item \\textbf{FinOps Strategy:} Designed credit-stacking approach achieving \\$0 infrastructure for 12-18 months through NVIDIA Inception, Nebius (\\$150K credits), AWS Activate, and Techstars programme eligibility.\n74: \\end{itemize}}\n75: \n76: \\cventry{April 2025--Sept 2025}{Technical Product Manager}{PRGRSS / Global Purpose Enterprise}{Remote / Hybrid}{}{\n77: \\begin{itemize}\n78:     \\item \\textbf{Product Leadership:} Orchestrated the product road-map for a novel career mentorship platform, managing a cross-functional development team across the UK and Pakistan. Reduced technical miscommunication by 60\\% through precise requirements documentation.\n79:     \\item \\textbf{Rapid Prototyping:} Utilised Lovable.dev to build high-fidelity prototypes for the ``Mentor Connect'' flow and Admin Dashboard, accelerating the MVP feedback loop.\n80:     \\item \\textbf{Stakeholder Engagement:} Represented the organisation at the National Grid headquarters in Warwick, presenting technical application capabilities to Employee Resource Groups (ERGs) with 20+ senior leaders alongside CEO, Spence.\n81: \\end{itemize}}\n82: \n83: \\cventry{Sept 2023--Aug 2024}{End User Computing (EUC) Desktop Support Technician}{University of South Wales}{Pontypridd}{}{\n84: \\begin{itemize}\n85:     \\item Provided comprehensive technical support for 3,000+ staff and 20,000+ students across multiple campuses, delivering first and second-line support while maintaining strict SLA compliance.\n86:     \\item Supported the transition from legacy ticketing system (POB) to Freshworks, ensuring seamless change management and ITIL-aligned service delivery processes.\n87:     \\item Managed user authentication and access control through Azure Active Directory, Microsoft 365 suite with Teams administration and user training.\n88:     \\item Supported virtual application delivery through AppsAnywhere platform, created user guides and support documentation.\n89:     \\item Implemented and maintained PaperCut print management system across campus locations.\n90:     \\item Completed Information Security Awareness and GDPR certification training (2023/24).\n91: \\end{itemize}}\n92: \n93: \\cventry{Sept 2023--Aug 2024}{Digital Technical Mentor}{University of South Wales}{Pontypridd}{}{\n94: \\begin{itemize}\n95:     \\item Delivered 15+ virtual/in-person training sessions on Microsoft 365 tools, Generative AI, e-Learning tools, Adobe Creative Cloud, and web-based apps.\n96:     \\item Created technical documentation reducing repetitive FAQ, whilst manning the University Study Skills department desk.\n97:     \\item Supported in-person shift patterns to provide continuous IT support coverage alongside EUC role and trained non-technically fluent Digital Mentor colleagues.\n98:     \\item Provided high-level technical consulting to PhD researchers, resolving complex Reference Management (EndNote) and AI-driven research methodologies.\n99: \\end{itemize}}\n100: \n101: \\cventry{July 2022--Aug 2024}{STEM Ambassador \\& Technical Trainer}{Technocamps / Central South Consortium (CSC)}{Wales}{}{\n102: \\begin{itemize}\n103:     \\item Delivered fortnightly workshops to Year 13 students on WJEC DigiTech A-Level Unit 4: Transactional Websites, focusing on e-commerce site development using wireframing (Figma), HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.\n104:     \\item Mentored students in UI/UX design principles, version control with GitHub, and fast prototyping using Bootstrap frameworks.\n105:     \\item Conducted CPD sessions for Welsh teachers, training them on transactional website development and practical teaching strategies for A-Level DigiTech curricula.\n106:     \\item Incorporated LEGO Education SPIKE Prime kits into STEM workshops to teach robotics, Python with block programming, and computational thinking.\n107:     \\item Advocated for ethical Generative AI use in education, researching ways to integrate AI tools effectively for neurodiverse learners.\n108:     \\item Engineered a hybrid learning environment using Linux bootable USB drives to meet exam board requirements.\n109: \\end{itemize}}\n110: \n111: \\cventry{June 2024--Aug 2024}{Web Migration Support \\& Digital Content Specialist}{University of South Wales}{Pontypridd}{}{\n112: \\begin{itemize}\n113:     \\item Collaborated with the Web and Digital Content Executive to execute Phase 1 migration of the USW ``Careers and Employability'' platform.\n114:     \\item Managed imagery and metadata, ensuring strict adherence to Welsh Language Standards for digital accessibility across the site architecture.\n115: \\end{itemize}}\n116: \n117: \\cventry{Sept 2020--Dec 2020}{Executive Assistant}{Nyfasi eCommerce}{Cardiff, UK}{}{\n118: \\begin{itemize}\n119:     \\item Supported Shopify-based eCommerce platform development and maintenance for Dr.\\ Youmna Mouhamad's Nyfasi Deluxe Detangler.\n120:     \\item Contributed to development and maintenance of the Shopify website, ensuring seamless user experience and successful sales.\n121:     \\item Assisted with digital marketing initiatives, R\\&D, and brand awareness campaigns.\n122:     \\item Helped Nyfasi launch its first 500 units with minimal investment through digital infrastructure readiness.\n123: \\end{itemize}}\n124: \n125: \\cventry{Sept 2018--Aug 2023}{Technical Solutions Provider}{Andrea Kwabena Technologies}{Italy / UK}{}{\n126: \\begin{itemize}\n127:     \\item Delivered technical support and system optimisation services (Windows, macOS, Android, Linux).\n128:     \\item Implemented cloud-based solutions for small business clients (Shopify, Squarespace, Wix).\n129:     \\item Created technical documentation and user training materials (MS 365 Suite, Canva Pro).\n130:     \\item Provided data recovery and system maintenance services (Kali Linux, Autopsy Digital Forensics).\n131:     \\item Built lasting client relationships through consistent service delivery.\n132: \\end{itemize}}\n133: \n134: \\cventry{June 2016--July 2020}{Checkout Customer Assistant}{Tesco Superstore}{Bristol, UK}{}{\n135: \\begin{itemize}\n136:     \\item Maintained exceptional service standards in high-volume retail environment serving 500+ customers daily, including shop floor and warehouse.\n137:     \\item Developed strong problem-solving and conflict resolution skills handling diverse customer needs.\n138:     \\item Trained new team members on POS systems and customer service protocols.\n139:     \\item Consistently received positive feedback for professional and efficient service.\n140: \\end{itemize}}\n141: \n142: \\section{Key Projects}\n143: \\cventry{2025--Present}{Getaway AI: Multi-Agent Travel Planning Platform}{}{}{}{Multi-agent AI system on AWS Bedrock with real-time itinerary generation, flight search, hotel booking, and activity recommendations. Built with Python, Lambda serverless functions, VPC networking, IAM policies, and Bedrock model orchestration. Deployed to production on AWS.}\n144: \\cventry{2024}{BSc Dissertation: RAG Coding Assistant}{}{}{}{``Levelling the Playing Field Using Generative AI Coding Assistant---an Implementation of RAG Architecture'' (First Class Honours). Built a teaching platform combining pre-trained Gen AI code assistance with traditional educational materials using Digital Ocean infrastructure, containerized AI models, Jupyter notebooks, and modern API architectures.}\n145: \\cventry{2024}{IT Infrastructure with SSO Integration}{}{}{}{Configured VMware Workstation Pro with Active Directory integration. Automated user provisioning across domain controllers using PowerShell. Built secure file servers integrating Windows and Linux systems.}\n146: \\cventry{2024}{Netlify Web Application}{}{}{}{Motorway services Single-Page Application built with vanilla HTML/CSS/JS: \\href{https://m25-cobham.netlify.app}{\\textcolor{accentgreen}{m25-cobham.netlify.app}}}\n147: \\cventry{2023}{WordPress Technical Hub}{}{}{}{Comprehensive technical resource hub for hardware configuration and guides: \\href{http://www.enneict.wordpress.com}{\\textcolor{accentgreen}{www.enneict.wordpress.com}}}\n148: \n149: \\section{Research, Leadership \\& Awards}\n150: \\cvitem{Marie Curie}{Key participant in the EU Horizon 2020 Marie Curie MIDIC Project (Grant 841716/874979). Research validated how Second Generation Individuals cultivate Intercultural Competence (IC) through bicultural navigation as a strategic labour market asset.}\n151: \\cvitem{BJS Feature}{Featured as ``Giovanni'' in the British Journal of Sociology (Varriale, Nov 2025): \\textit{``Meritocracy, Recognition and Double Consciousness.''}}\n152: \\cvitem{Board Advisory}{Community Board Member \\& Tech Strategist for FirstGens CIC; architected the data strategy and Notion-based PWA infrastructure underpinning the 2023-24 Impact Report. Consulted on the official UCAS First-Generation Students Guidance launched nationally in 2024.}\n153: \\cvitem{Facilitator}{Lead facilitator for the ``Demystifying AI'' event at Tramshed Tech, in partnership with BYP Network.}\n154: \\cvitem{BYP Network}{Cardiff Co-Lead for BYP Network (Black Young Professionals). Suggested ``scrum route'' for BYP onboarding and community engagement.}\n155: \\cvitem{Award}{Awarded ``Best Networker'' at the USW Freelancers Academy (2019).}\n156: \n157: \\section{Education \\& Certifications}\n158: \\cventry{Sept 2024}{AWS Cloud Engineering re/Start Bootcamp}{Cardiff and Vale College}{}{}{Cloud-native application design, network architecture, security, Python automation, VPC networking, native cloud security.}\n159: \\cventry{June 2024}{BSc (Hons) Information Communication Technology}{University of South Wales}{}{2:1}{Dissertation: ``Levelling the Playing Field Using Generative AI Coding Assistant---an Implementation of RAG Architecture'' (First Class Honours). Core Modules: IT Service Management (85\\%); Applied Computer Networking (87\\%); Advanced Databases and Modelling (68\\%).}\n160: \\cventry{June 2016}{ICT BTEC Level 3 Extended Diploma}{Bradley Stoke Community School}{Bristol}{DDM}{Specialised in IT Systems Support and Troubleshooting.}\n161: \\cventry{2016}{GCSEs}{Bradley Stoke Community School}{Bristol}{}{Italian (A*); French (B); IT (Qcf) BTEC (D*); Maths (C); Additional Science (B); Core Sciences (D).}\n162: \n163: \\section{Technical Skills Matrix}\n164: \\cvitem{Cloud \\& AI}{AWS (Bedrock, Lambda, VPC, IAM, S3, CloudFormation, API Gateway); NVIDIA Inception (NIM APIs, Speech NIM); Azure (AD, Virtual Desktop, Microsoft 365); GCP; Oracle Cloud (Always Free Tier); Docker; Kubernetes.}\n165: \\cvitem{Development}{Python (FastAPI/Pandas); JavaScript (React/Next.js); HTML5/CSS3 (Bootstrap); Git/GitHub; MySQL; PowerShell; Bash; VB.NET; C\\#; Tailwind CSS; LaTeX.}\n166: \\cvitem{Systems}{VMware Workstation; Splashtop; AppsAnywhere; Linux CLI; Android; VS Code/Enterprise; IntelliJ IDEA; Wazuh SIEM.}\n167: \\cvitem{CMS}{Shopify; WordPress; Terminalfour; Sanity CMS; Drupal; Joomla; cPanel.}\n168: \\cvitem{Collaboration}{Microsoft Teams; Slack; Zoom; Google Meet; Discord; Mattermost; Linear; Jira; GitHub Projects.}\n169: \\cvitem{Personal}{Semi-professional Drummer (ad-hoc tutor); English (Native); Italian (Native); Akan/Twi (Conversational); Avid Reader; Intercultural Competence Speaker and Facilitator.}\n170: \n171: \\end{document}\n\n(End of file - total 171 lines)\n</content>",
