      "text": "I found your master CV at `C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\Downloads\\Andrea_Enning_Master_CV.tex`. Here is the full parsed content:\n\n**Andrea Enning**  \nCo-Founder & Cloud Architect | AI-Native Product Lead | AWS Certified  \nNottinghamshire, United Kingdom  \n+44 07480 261369 | andiekobbietks@outlook.com  \nlinkedin.com/in/andiekobbietks | github.com/andiekobbietks\n\n---\n\n### Professional Profile\n* Co-Founder & Cloud Architect of Getaway AI, a multi-agent group travel planning application deployed on AWS Bedrock with real-time itinerary generation. Built and shipped the production system from architecture to deployment, managing the full infrastructure lifecycle including VPC design, IAM policies, Lambda orchestration, and Bedrock model integration. Conceived the product, recruited the team, secured resources, and continued development solo after the technical co-founder departed in September 2025.\n* AWS re/Start graduate with hands-on cloud engineering expertise spanning VPC networking, IAM policy design, Lambda serverless architecture, and infrastructure-as-code automation. Dissertation—an AI teaching assistant using RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) architecture—achieved First Class Honours. Brings 18+ months of insider access to Tramshed Tech (Cardiff's largest tech hub), BYP Network co-lead position, and AWS Activate credits secured for Getaway AI.\n* Published contributor to the EU Horizon 2020 Marie Curie MIDIC Project and the British Journal of Sociology, validating high-level Intercultural Competence (IC) and strategic navigation of complex socio-technical landscapes. Community Board Member & Tech Strategist for FirstGens CIC, architecting the data strategy underpinning their 2023-24 Impact Report and UCAS First-Generation Students Guidance.\n\n### Core Competencies\n* **Cloud & AI:** AWS Bedrock (Nova Lite, Haiku 4.5, Sonnet 4.6), Lambda, VPC, IAM, S3, CloudFormation, API Gateway; NVIDIA Inception (NIM APIs); Azure Active Directory; GCP; Oracle Cloud Always Free Tier; RAG Architecture; Prompt Engineering; Multi-Agent Orchestration.\n* **Software Dev:** Python (FastAPI/Pandas), JavaScript (React/Next.js), HTML5/CSS3, Git/GitHub, MySQL, PowerShell, Bash, Docker, Kubernetes, VMware, LAMP Stack, API Design, Agile/Scrum.\n* **Security & Ops:** Wazuh SIEM (Zero Trust Architecture), Azure Active Directory, Microsoft 365 Admin, GDPR Compliance, Information Security Awareness, ITIL Best Practices.\n* **Training & Leadership:** Curriculum Design (WJEC/IfATE), CPD Delivery, Formative Assessment, Stakeholder Management, Cross-Functional Team Leadership, Public Speaking, Intercultural Competence.\n\n### Professional Experience\n**Co-Founder & Cloud Architect** | Getaway AI | Remote / Nottinghamshire | Sept 2025–Present\n* Conceived, designed, and shipped a multi-agent group travel planning application with real-time itinerary generation, flight search, hotel booking, and activity recommendations powered by AWS Bedrock AI models.\n* Designed and deployed the full AWS infrastructure including VPC networking, IAM policy management, Lambda serverless functions, S3 storage, API Gateway endpoints, and Bedrock model orchestration for Nova Lite, Claude Haiku 4.5, and Sonnet 4.6.\n* Sole technical decision-maker after co-founder departure; managed product roadmap, security architecture, and deployment pipeline. Secured AWS Activate credits ($5,000) and NVIDIA Inception membership.\n* Built GitHub repository (Getaway-AI-Assistant) with multi-agent orchestration, integrated MCP Apps for distribution, and developed scratchpad skill for zero-config coding assistance.\n* Designed credit-stacking approach achieving $0 infrastructure for 12-18 months through NVIDIA Inception, Nebius ($150K credits), AWS Activate, and Techstars programme eligibility.\n\n**Technical Product Manager** | PRGRSS / Global Purpose Enterprise | Remote / Hybrid | April 2025–Sept 2025\n* Orchestrated the product road-map for a novel career mentorship platform, managing a cross-functional development team across the UK and Pakistan. Reduced technical miscommunication by 60% through precise requirements documentation.\n* Utilised Lovable.dev to build high-fidelity prototypes for the \"Mentor Connect\" flow and Admin Dashboard, accelerating the MVP feedback loop.\n* Represented the organisation at the National Grid headquarters in Warwick, presenting technical application capabilities to Employee Resource Groups (ERGs) with 20+ senior leaders alongside CEO, Spence.\n\n**End User Computing (EUC) Desktop Support Technician** | University of South Wales | Pontypridd | Sept 2023–Aug 2024\n* Provided comprehensive technical support for 3,000+ staff and 20,000+ students across multiple campuses, delivering first and second-line support while maintaining strict SLA compliance.\n* Supported the transition from legacy ticketing system (POB) to Freshworks, ensuring seamless change management and ITIL-aligned service delivery processes.\n* Managed user authentication and access control through Azure Active Directory, Microsoft 365 suite with Teams administration and user training.\n* Supported virtual application delivery through AppsAnywhere platform, created user guides and support documentation.\n* Implemented and maintained PaperCut print management system across campus locations.\n* Completed Information Security Awareness and GDPR certification training (2023/24).\n\n**Digital Technical Mentor** | University of South Wales | Pontypridd | Sept 2023–Aug 2024\n* Delivered 15+ virtual/in-person training sessions on Microsoft 365 tools, Generative AI, e-Learning tools, Adobe Creative Cloud, and web-based apps.\n* Created technical documentation reducing repetitive FAQ, whilst manning the University Study Skills department desk.\n* Supported in-person shift patterns to provide continuous IT support coverage alongside EUC role and trained non-technically fluent Digital Mentor colleagues.\n* Provided high-level technical consulting to PhD researchers, resolving complex Reference Management (EndNote) and AI-driven research methodologies.\n\n**STEM Ambassador & Technical Trainer** | Technocamps / Central South Consortium (CSC) | Wales | July 2022–Aug 2024\n* Delivered fortnightly workshops to Year 13 students on WJEC DigiTech A-Level Unit 4: Transactional Websites, focusing on e-commerce site development using wireframing (Figma), HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.\n* Mentored students in UI/UX design principles, version control with GitHub, and fast prototyping using Bootstrap frameworks.\n* Conducted CPD sessions for Welsh teachers, training them on transactional website development and practical teaching strategies for A-Level DigiTech curricula.\n* Incorporated LEGO Education SPIKE Prime kits into STEM workshops to teach robotics, Python with block programming, and computational thinking.\n* Advocated for ethical Generative AI use in education, researching ways to integrate AI tools effectively for neurodiverse learners.\n* Engineered a hybrid learning environment using Linux bootable USB drives to meet exam board requirements.\n\n**Web Migration Support & Digital Content Specialist** | University of South Wales | Pontypridd | June 2024–Aug 2024\n* Collaborated with the Web and Digital Content Executive to execute Phase 1 migration of the USW \"Careers and Employability\" platform.\n* Managed imagery and metadata, ensuring strict adherence to Welsh Language Standards for digital accessibility across the site architecture.\n\n**Executive Assistant** | Nyfasi eCommerce | Cardiff, UK | Sept 2020–Dec 2020\n* Supported Shopify-based eCommerce platform development and maintenance for Dr. Youmna Mouhamad's Nyfasi Deluxe Detangler.\n* Contributed to development and maintenance of the Shopify website, ensuring seamless user experience and successful sales.\n* Assisted with digital marketing initiatives, R&D, and brand awareness campaigns.\n* Helped Nyfasi launch its first 500 units with minimal investment through digital infrastructure readiness.\n\n**Technical Solutions Provider** | Andrea Kwabena Technologies | Italy / UK | Sept 2018–Aug 2023\n* Delivered technical support and system optimisation services (Windows, macOS, Android, Linux).\n* Implemented cloud-based solutions for small business clients (Shopify, Squarespace, Wix).\n* Created technical documentation and user training materials (MS 365 Suite, Canva Pro).\n* Provided data recovery and system maintenance services (Kali Linux, Autopsy Digital Forensics).\n* Built lasting client relationships through consistent service delivery.\n\n**Checkout Customer Assistant** | Tesco Superstore | Bristol, UK | June 2016–July 2020\n* Maintained exceptional service standards in high-volume retail environment serving 500+ customers daily, including shop floor and warehouse.\n* Developed strong problem-solving and conflict resolution skills handling diverse customer needs.\n* Trained new team members on POS systems and customer service protocols.\n* Consistently received positive feedback for professional and efficient service.\n\n### Key Projects\n* **Getaway AI: Multi-Agent Travel Planning Platform** (2025–Present): Multi-agent AI system on AWS Bedrock with real-time itinerary generation, flight search, hotel booking, and activity recommendations. Built with Python, Lambda serverless functions, VPC networking, IAM policies, and Bedrock model orchestration. Deployed to production on AWS.\n* **BSc Dissertation: RAG Coding Assistant** (2024): \"Levelling the Playing Field Using Generative AI Coding Assistant—an Implementation of RAG Architecture\" (First Class Honours). Built a teaching platform combining pre-trained Gen AI code assistance with traditional educational materials using Digital Ocean infrastructure, containerized AI models, Jupyter notebooks, and modern API architectures.\n* **IT Infrastructure with SSO Integration** (2024): Configured VMware Workstation Pro with Active Directory integration. Automated user provisioning across domain controllers using PowerShell. Built secure file servers integrating Windows and Linux systems.\n* **Netlify Web Application** (2024): Motorway services Single-Page Application built with vanilla HTML/CSS/JS: m25-cobham.netlify.app\n* **WordPress Technical Hub** (2023): Comprehensive technical resource hub for hardware configuration and guides: www.enneict.wordpress.com\n\n### Research, Leadership & Awards\n* **Marie Curie:** Key participant in the EU Horizon 2020 Marie Curie MIDIC Project (Grant 841716/874979). Research validated how Second Generation Individuals cultivate Intercultural Competence (IC) through bicultural navigation as a strategic labour market asset.\n* **BJS Feature:** Featured as \"Giovanni\" in the British Journal of Sociology (Varriale, Nov 2025): \"Meritocracy, Recognition and Double Consciousness.\"\n* **Board Advisory:** Community Board Member & Tech Strategist for FirstGens CIC; architected the data strategy and Notion-based PWA infrastructure underpinning the 2023-24 Impact Report. Consulted on the official UCAS First-Generation Students Guidance launched nationally in 2024.\n* **Facilitator:** Lead facilitator for the \"Demystifying AI\" event at Tramshed Tech, in partnership with BYP Network.\n* **BYP Network:** Cardiff Co-Lead for BYP Network (Black Young Professionals). Suggested \"scrum route\" for BYP onboarding and community engagement.\n* **Award:** Awarded \"Best Networker\" at the USW Freelancers Academy (2019).\n\n### Education & Certifications\n* **AWS Cloud Engineering re/Start Bootcamp** | Cardiff and Vale College | Sept 2024: Cloud-native application design, network architecture, security, Python automation, VPC networking, native cloud security.\n* **BSc (Hons) Information Communication Technology** | University of South Wales | June 2024 | 2:1: Dissertation: \"Levelling the Playing Field Using Generative AI Coding Assistant—an Implementation of RAG Architecture\" (First Class Honours). Core Modules: IT Service Management (85%); Applied Computer Networking (87%); Advanced Databases and Modelling (68%).\n* **ICT BTEC Level 3 Extended Diploma** | Bradley Stoke Community School, Bristol | June 2016 | DDM: Specialised in IT Systems Support and Troubleshooting.\n* **GCSEs** | Bradley Stoke Community School, Bristol | 2016: Italian (A*); French (B); IT (Qcf) BTEC (D*); Maths (C); Additional Science (B); Core Sciences (D).\n\n### Technical Skills Matrix\n* **Cloud & AI:** AWS (Bedrock, Lambda, VPC, IAM, S3, CloudFormation, API Gateway); NVIDIA Inception (NIM APIs, Speech NIM); Azure (AD, Virtual Desktop, Microsoft 365); GCP; Oracle Cloud (Always Free Tier); Docker; Kubernetes.\n* **Development:** Python (FastAPI/Pandas); JavaScript (React/Next.js); HTML5/CSS3 (Bootstrap); Git/GitHub; MySQL; PowerShell; Bash; VB.NET; C#; Tailwind CSS; LaTeX.\n* **Systems:** VMware Workstation; Splashtop; AppsAnywhere; Linux CLI; Android; VS Code/Enterprise; IntelliJ IDEA; Wazuh SIEM.\n* **CMS:** Shopify; WordPress; Terminalfour; Sanity CMS; Drupal; Joomla; cPanel.\n* **Collaboration:** Microsoft Teams; Slack; Zoom; Google Meet; Discord; Mattermost; Linear; Jira; GitHub Projects.\n* **Personal:** Semi-professional Drummer (ad-hoc tutor); English (Native); Italian (Native); Akan/Twi (Conversational); Avid Reader; Intercultural Competence Speaker and Facilitator.",
